				<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p><font color="#ff57f1">Google Analytics is not designed for mobile apps.</font> In fact, it is very difficult for you to get actionable reports about your mobile app using Google Analytics data. For that, you need Firebase. </p>



<p>Google Analytics for <font color="#ff57f1">Firebase is specially designed for mobile apps. </font> It is optimized to track the performance of your mobile app with more than 500 parameters. See the video below to find out more about this amazing platform.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<div class="video-container"><iframe class='youtube-player' type='text/html' width='640' height='360' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=PLl-K7zZEsYLmOF_07IayrTntevxtbUxDL&#038;hl=en_US' allowfullscreen='true' style='border:0;'></iframe></div>
</div></figure>



<p>We are excited to announce that we have successfully completed the legwork that allows you to <font color="#ff57f1">integrate Firebase Analytics into your Andromo app with just two clicks.</font> Yes, it&#8217;s that simple!</p>



<h2>Get better insights on your users </h2>



<p>Firebase Analytics gives you data about how your users interact with your app. You can track a wide array of behaviors from downloads to shares, to actions such as using the camera for a selfie in your app and more. These are almost all impossible in Google Analytics. </p>



<p>This data will help you plan and make better product development decisions. You can <font color="#ff57f1">market more accurately,</font> as well as optimize your app without worrying about spending resources on things your users won&#8217;t use.</p>



<p>Firebase also shows crash data, notification effectiveness, deep-link performance, in-app purchase data, and more in <font color="#ff57f1">real-time. </font></p>



<h2>Ad Network Revenue tracking</h2>



<p>Get more from Firebase by linking your AdMob account. Firebase Analytics reports merge with ad metrics and AdMob revenue, showing you the real lifetime value of your users, as well as the performance of your in-app advertising campaigns. With this, you will <font color="#ff57f1">know who exactly your target audience is,</font> and target them more effectively.</p>



<h2>Unparalleled Segmentation and Targeting</h2>



<p>Fine-tune your targeting with unmatched precision. Create Firebase custom audiences based on device data and user behavior. Using events and user properties, you can define highly targeted segments for notifications, A/B tests (with <a href="https://firebase.google.com/products/remote-config">Firebase Remote Config</a>), and remarketing. If you want to take your analysis to the next level, export your raw data to <a href="https://cloud.google.com/bigquery">BigQuery</a>. That&#8217;s a topic for another day.</p>



<h2>Setting up Firebase on Andromo</h2>



<p>Enabling Firebase Analytics on your Andromo mobile app is very easy. <font color="#ff57f1">No coding or complex steps are required.</font> Please note that for this to work, you will need a Google Firebase account. If you don‚Äôt have one, create your account <a href="https://firebase.google.com">here</a>.<br></p>



<p><strong>First, you‚Äôll need to add your app to Firebase.</strong><br>Log in to your Firebase account and go to your console. On your console‚Äôs left panel navigation, click on Analytics to expand the menu and then select ‚ÄòDashboard‚Äô.<br><br><img scale="0" class="wp-image-5059" style="width: 1000px;" src="https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dashboard-Firebase.png?ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dashboard-Firebase.png?w=2560&amp;ssl=1 2560w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dashboard-Firebase.png?resize=600%2C259&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dashboard-Firebase.png?resize=768%2C332&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dashboard-Firebase.png?resize=1000%2C432&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dashboard-Firebase.png?w=2000&amp;ssl=1 2000w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /><br></p>



<p><strong>Select Android, to add your app.</strong><br><br><img scale="0" class="wp-image-5062" style="width: 400px;" src="https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Add-an-app.png?ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Add-an-app.png?w=826&amp;ssl=1 826w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Add-an-app.png?resize=600%2C376&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Add-an-app.png?resize=768%2C481&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 826px) 100vw, 826px" data-recalc-dims="1" /><br></p>



<p><strong>Enter the package name of your app on the succeeding screen and then click ‚ÄúRegister app&#8221;, then download the config file.</strong><br><br><img scale="0" class="wp-image-5064" style="width: 1000px;" src="https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Register-app-Firebase.png?ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Register-app-Firebase.png?w=1928&amp;ssl=1 1928w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Register-app-Firebase.png?resize=600%2C411&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Register-app-Firebase.png?resize=768%2C527&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/blog.andromo.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Register-app-Firebase.png?resize=1000%2C686&amp;ssl=1 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /><br></p>
